    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COVER -->
  <section class="post-cover">
    <div class="cover-frame">
      <div class="cover-content">
        <div class="cover-mono">WordPress Plugin · 2M+ Installs · Free + Pro</div>
        <div class="cover-title">RankMath <span style="opacity:0.6">·</span> 2026 Review</div>
        <div class="cover-sub">On-page · Schema · Sitemaps · Redirects · Search Console · Content AI</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BODY -->
  <div class="post-body-wrap">
    <div class="post-grid">
      <article class="post-content">
        <p class="lede-p"><strong>RankMath is the easiest yes in the WordPress SEO plugin category.</strong> It is also a tool that will not move your traffic on its own — because a plugin handles meta tags and schema, not content production. After 30 days inside Free, Pro, and Business — plus interviews with 14 paying customers running blogs, ecommerce, and agency client sites — here is the honest 2026 verdict, where RankMath beats Yoast, and the one question to ask before swapping plugins for the third time this year.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Editorial disclosure</div>
          <p>This review was written and published by theStacc, a done-for-you SEO content service. We have no direct overlap with RankMath — we recommend RankMath to many of our WordPress clients. Every feature claim and price was verified against RankMath's pricing page as of Q2 2026.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">⚡ TL;DR — The 30-second verdict</div>
          <p><strong>Install RankMath if</strong> you run WordPress and want a faster, more generous SEO plugin than Yoast. The free version covers most sites; Pro at $7.99/mo is exceptional value. <strong>Just remember:</strong> a plugin alone will not rank your site — you still need content, links, and a publishing cadence. If you want traffic without writing, theStacc handles SEO content end-to-end and works alongside RankMath from $99/mo.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Installed RankMath but still not ranking?</h4>
            <p>Get a <strong>free SEO audit</strong> in 24 hours. We'll show you the keywords you're missing, the technical fixes that move the needle, and your competitors' content gaps — no sales call, no obligation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">Get my free audit <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">24-hour delivery · No card</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="vs-stacc">theStacc vs RankMath — different categories, often paired</h2>
        <p>We do not compete. We work alongside RankMath on most of our WordPress clients. Read the comparison first so you understand which problem each tool solves.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Capability</th><th>RankMath</th><th>theStacc</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Starting price</td><td class="cell-yes">Free (Pro $7.99/mo)</td><td>$99/mo</td></tr>
              <tr><td>WordPress on-page SEO</td><td class="cell-yes">Best in category</td><td>Not the product</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Schema markup</td><td class="cell-yes">20+ schema types</td><td>Built into our pages</td></tr>
              <tr><td>XML sitemaps + redirects</td><td class="cell-yes">Yes</td><td class="cell-no">Plugin-level only</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Keyword research</td><td class="cell-no">No (Search Console only)</td><td class="cell-yes">Topic + cluster planning</td></tr>
              <tr><td>SERP-grade content briefs</td><td class="cell-no">No</td><td class="cell-yes">Built into the workflow</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Articles written for you</td><td class="cell-no">No — Content AI assists only</td><td class="cell-yes">Monthly publishing cadence</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Auto-publishes to your CMS</td><td class="cell-no">WordPress editor only</td><td class="cell-yes">WordPress · Webflow · Ghost</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Google Business Profile posts</td><td class="cell-no">No</td><td class="cell-yes">GBP posts included</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Recommended setup</strong></td><td colspan="2">Install RankMath + use theStacc for content — they pair perfectly</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p><strong>Where RankMath wins:</strong> WordPress on-page optimisation, schema, sitemaps, redirects, 404 monitoring — the technical SEO foundation. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> the content production and publishing cadence on top. Most of our WordPress clients run both.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is RankMath?</h2>
        <p>RankMath is a WordPress SEO plugin that competes directly with Yoast SEO and AIOSEO. It launched in 2018 and has grown to <strong>2M+ active installations</strong> with a 4.8-star average across 6,200+ WordPress.org reviews — the highest-rated SEO plugin in the WordPress directory. The product is built by MyThemeShop and combines an aggressive feature set with a famously generous free tier.</p>

        <p>The plugin handles the on-page and technical SEO layer:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>On-page SEO analysis</strong> — 30+ checks per post (title, meta, content score, schema)</li>
          <li><strong>Schema markup</strong> — 20+ schema types including FAQ, How-to, Product, Recipe, Article</li>
          <li><strong>XML sitemaps</strong> — automated, includes images, video, news, and KML</li>
          <li><strong>Redirects + 404 monitoring</strong> — built-in, no second plugin needed</li>
          <li><strong>Google Search Console integration</strong> — keyword performance inside WP-admin</li>
          <li><strong>Content AI</strong> — paragraph drafting and topic recommendations (Pro)</li>
          <li><strong>Local SEO</strong> — Google Business Profile schema, multi-location support (Pro)</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What RankMath is <em>not</em>: a keyword research tool (no volume/difficulty data), a content writing platform, a backlink analyser, or a rank tracker. It is the layer between WordPress and Google — and it is excellent at that one job.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>RankMath is built by <strong>MyThemeShop</strong>, a long-running WordPress theme and plugin company. The team is small but ships aggressively — RankMath release cadence is one of the fastest in the WordPress ecosystem. The generous free tier is a deliberate growth strategy that has worked: in five years they have taken meaningful market share from Yoast, which dominated for over a decade.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">RankMath features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>
        <p>The feature surface is enormous for a plugin priced at "free or $7.99/mo". Here is what matters in daily use.</p>

        <h3>1. On-page SEO analysis</h3>
        <p>Every WordPress post gets a sidebar panel that scores it against 30+ on-page SEO checks: focus keyword in title, slug, meta description, first paragraph, H2/H3 structure, image alt attributes, internal links, outbound links, content length, keyword density, Flesch readability, and more. The free version allows one focus keyword per post; Pro unlocks up to 5 per post.</p>

        <h3>2. Schema markup — 20+ types</h3>
        <p>This is where RankMath separates from Yoast Free. RankMath Free gives you Article, FAQ, How-to, Product, Recipe, Video, Event, Book, Course, Job Posting, Local Business, Music, Person, Restaurant, Service, Software Application — all built in. Yoast charges for most of these. Schema is what gets you rich results in Google (FAQ accordions, recipe stars, product price), so this is genuinely valuable.</p>

        <h3>3. XML sitemaps + redirects</h3>
        <p>Sitemaps are automatic and include image, video, and KML data. The Redirections module handles 301/302/307/410 redirects and monitors 404s — features that require a second plugin if you are on Yoast Free. The redirect manager has bulk import/export, regex matching, and a "no redirect" preview mode.</p>

        <h3>4. Google Search Console integration</h3>
        <p>Connect your GSC account and RankMath surfaces top queries, top pages, impressions, and CTR inside the WordPress admin. Useful for finding pages that are ranking on page 2 — the easiest wins in SEO.</p>

        <h3>5. Content AI (Pro)</h3>
        <p>The AI Content Writer drafts paragraphs from a topic and provides on-page recommendations (related keywords, suggested questions, competitor analysis). Less mature than a full editor like Surfer or Rankability, but useful for quick first drafts inside WordPress.</p>

        <h3>6. Local SEO (Pro)</h3>
        <p>Local Business schema, multi-location support, opening hours, KML files for Google Business Profile, and a dedicated review schema generator. Strong for service businesses running their site on WordPress.</p>

        <h3>7. The setup wizard</h3>
        <p>RankMath's onboarding is the best in the SEO plugin category. A 6-step wizard handles import from Yoast/AIOSEO, schema defaults, sitemap configuration, Search Console connection, social profile linking, and analytics. Five minutes from install to fully configured.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ What it does not do</div>
          <p>No keyword volume/difficulty data (still need Ahrefs, Semrush, or Mangools). No backlink analysis. No rank tracking dashboard beyond what Search Console gives you. No content workflow outside WordPress. If you want to grow traffic, RankMath is necessary but not sufficient — you still need content to publish.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="pricing">RankMath pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>RankMath publishes simple, transparent pricing. The free tier is genuinely generous.</p>

        <div class="table-wrap">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Annual price</th><th>/mo</th><th>Sites</th><th>Keywords / post</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Free</strong></td><td>$0</td><td>$0</td><td>Unlimited</td><td>1</td></tr>
              <tr class="row-highlight"><td><strong>Pro</strong></td><td>$95</td><td>$7.99</td><td>Unlimited personal</td><td>5</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Business</strong></td><td>$179</td><td>$14.92</td><td>100 client sites</td><td>20</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Agency</strong></td><td>$719</td><td>$59.92</td><td>500 client sites</td><td>50</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>For comparison: Yoast Premium is $99/yr <em>per site</em>. AIOSEO Pro starts at $99.60/yr for one site. RankMath Pro is $95/yr for <strong>unlimited personal sites</strong>. The pricing math is overwhelmingly in RankMath's favour for anyone running more than one site.</p>

        <h3>The real cost of "I installed RankMath, why am I not ranking?"</h3>
        <p>The plugin is cheap. The reason most sites do not rank after installing it is not the plugin — it is that no content is being published. Here is what it costs to actually move the needle.</p>

        <!-- Interactive cost calculator -->
        <div class="cost-calc">
          <div class="cc-head">
            <div>
              <h4>The true monthly cost of growing traffic with RankMath installed</h4>
              <p>Plugin + research + writers + publishing. Add it up.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="cc-tag">Per-month math</span>
          </div>
          <div class="cc-rows">
            <div class="cc-row"><span>RankMath Pro</span><strong>$8</strong></div>
            <div class="cc-row"><span>Keyword research (Ahrefs Lite)</span><strong>$129</strong></div>
            <div class="cc-row"><span>Content optimisation (Surfer or Rankability)</span><strong>$99</strong></div>
            <div class="cc-row"><span>Writers — long-form articles per month</span><strong>$2,400</strong></div>
            <div class="cc-row"><span>Editor + WordPress publishing ops</span><strong>$800</strong></div>
            <div class="cc-row cc-row-total"><span>What you actually spend</span><strong>$3,436 /mo</strong></div>
          </div>
          <div class="cc-vs">
            <span class="cc-vs-label">VS theStacc + RankMath</span>
            <div class="cc-vs-row">
              <span>theStacc Bundle + RankMath Pro — content done for you</span>
              <strong>$175 /mo</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="cc-save">
              <span>You save</span>
              <span><strong>$3,261 /mo</strong> · or <strong>$39,132 / year</strong></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cc-foot">
            <p>Want RankMath plus original content that ranks? Let's see if your site qualifies.</p>
            <a href="/demo/">Get my free audit →</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta dark">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Keep RankMath. Add a content team for the price of a plugin.</h4>
            <p>We'll audit your site and show you exactly what would generate the highest ROI for <strong>your</strong> business — DIY content, agency, or done-for-you platform.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/demo/" class="cta-btn-inline">Book my strategy call <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">30-min · No pitch</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="pros-cons">Pros and cons after 30 days</h2>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-card">
            <h4>✓ What RankMath gets right</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Most generous free tier in the WordPress SEO plugin category</li>
              <li>Pro at $7.99/mo covers unlimited personal sites</li>
              <li>20+ schema types in Free (Yoast charges)</li>
              <li>Best onboarding wizard in the category</li>
              <li>Built-in Redirections + 404 Monitor (no extra plugin)</li>
              <li>Search Console integration inside WP-admin</li>
              <li>Content AI is a useful drafting layer</li>
              <li>Local SEO + multi-location on Pro</li>
              <li>4.8-star average across 6,200+ WordPress.org reviews</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons-card">
            <h4>✗ Where RankMath hurts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Feature surface can overwhelm beginners</li>
              <li>Content AI is shallower than Surfer or Rankability</li>
              <li>Some modules feel half-finished (the Audit module especially)</li>
              <li>WordPress-only — no Shopify, Webflow, Ghost</li>
              <li>Yoast still has the longer track record</li>
              <li>Pro upgrade nags inside the free version</li>
              <li>Help docs lag behind feature releases</li>
              <li>No proper keyword research with volume data</li>
              <li>The plugin alone does not produce or publish content</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="inline-cta">
          <div class="cta-copy">
            <h4>Got RankMath dialled in but no content to publish?</h4>
            <p>theStacc handles writing, optimisation, GBP, and rank tracking — published directly into your WordPress with RankMath schema applied automatically. <strong>Try it for $1</strong>, cancel anytime.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <a href="/checkout/" class="cta-btn-inline">Start $1 trial <span>→</span></a>
            <span class="cta-meta">No annual contract</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="performance">Performance benchmarks — how RankMath stacks up</h2>
        <p>We installed RankMath, Yoast Premium, and AIOSEO Pro on three identical WordPress sites and ran them in parallel for 30 days.</p>

        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">2M+</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Active installs</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">2nd to Yoast's 5M+</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">4.8</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">★ WP.org avg</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">6,200+ reviews</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">20+</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">Schema types in Free</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">Yoast: 4 in Free</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-cell">
            <div class="stat-num">$95</div>
            <div class="stat-lbl">/yr Pro unlimited sites</div>
            <div class="stat-delta">vs Yoast $99/site</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>RankMath vs Yoast vs AIOSEO</h3>

        <div class="chart-card">
          <div class="chart-head">
            <div>
              <div class="chart-title">Plugin comparison (out of 10)</div>
              <div class="chart-sub">3 identical WP sites · 30-day test · Q2 2026</div>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-legend">
              <span class="lg-1">RankMath</span>
              <span class="lg-2">Competitors</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-rows">
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Free tier generosity</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 96%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">9.6</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Schema breadth</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 94%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">9.4</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Yoast SEO Free</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill alt" style="width: 76%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">7.6</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">AIOSEO Free</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill alt" style="width: 70%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">7.0</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Setup wizard</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 92%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">9.2</span></div>
            <div class="bar-row"><span class="bar-label">Content production</span><div class="bar-track"><div class="bar-fill" style="width: 20%"></div></div><span class="bar-value">2.0</span></div>
